http://www.laboratorioazul.com.ar
<rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar>

[Ramon commented as follows: "We have been very busy. This is the 8th anthrax outbreak this year [2013] and as winter approaches we can expect more. It is the 3rd outbreak in Partido of Laprida with the same number in Olavarria. The flooding during the previous autumn-winter of 2012 and this summer's drought have produced special conditions along with a widespread failure to vaccinate the cattle. Recent information being processed indicates that in our Zone of Alert & Response only 14 per cent of the cattle have been vaccinated voluntarily, (85 974 of 601 154 animals). It seems we will continue to find animals dead from anthrax and people with cutaneous lesions on their hands and arms. Without doubt my voice is alone in the wilderness."

A busy time made worse by owners not vaccinating, in spite of being in a high risk area. Our thanks to Ramon.

For a map of Argentina showing the province of Buenos Aires, go to http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg
For Olavarria, go to http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/Olavarria.html.
For Laprida, go to http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/Laprida.html. - Mod.MHJ]
